{"questionId":"17423","questionHtml":"<p>A geometric sequence has&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_4} =&nbsp; - 70\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>u</mi> <mn>4</mn> </msub> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mn>70</mn> </math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_7} = 8.75\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>u</mi> <mn>7</mn> </msub> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>8.75</mn> </math></span>.&nbsp;Find the second term of the sequence.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_1}{r^3} =&nbsp; - 70\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>u</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> </mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mi>r</mi> <mn>3</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mn>70</mn> </math></span>,&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_1}{r^6} = 8.75\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>u</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> </mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mi>r</mi> <mn>6</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>8.75</mn> </math></span><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{r^3} = \\frac{{8.75}}{{ - 70}} =&nbsp; - 0.125\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>r</mi> <mn>3</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>8.75</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>70</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mn>0.125</mn> </math></span><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow r =&nbsp; - 0.5\"> <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo> <mi>r</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mn>0.5</mn> </math></span><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>valid attempt to find&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_2}\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>u</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </mrow> </math></span><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>for example:&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_1} = \\frac{{ - 70}}{{ - 0.125}} = 560\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>u</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>70</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>0.125</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mn>560</mn> </math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_2} = 560 \\times&nbsp; - 0.5\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>u</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>560</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mn>0.5</mn> </math></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" =&nbsp; - 280\"> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mn>280</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17423","referenceCode":"19N.2.AHL.TZ0.H_1","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"A geometric sequence has u 4 = − 70 and u 7 = 8.75 . Find the second term of the sequence.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"H_1","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.3—Geometric sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}